I have to give them 1 star due to their Covid cautions. I call every restaurant to find out their Covid regulations and if they are wearing masks.  South Cape Diner informed me all staff was masked. Fantastic. I want to support local businesses, especially during this time. I've eaten their 3 times in 6 weeks. And their food is delicious, best burger I've ever eaten in 46 yrs of eating.  So we've felt very comfortable going out for breakfast or lunch. Yesterday, we took the back entrance out and  kitchen staff are not wearing masks. Your kitchen staff is cooking my food without masks on? So why are you lying to your customer's? I have pictures so don't try deny it. This diner deserves 5 stars, their food is great, top-notch servers and fair prices. But during a global pandemic you cannot lie to your customer's. So either mask your entire staff or lose customers until after Covid-19. I just won't eat another mushroom, swiss blue cheese crumble burger until Covid-19 is under control. Sorry South Cape but lying to customers is not a smart thing to do during Covid-19. You have a lot of elderly customers and normal customers relying on you to follow CDC guidelines and to relay that info truthfully to your customer's. Mask up or see you in a year!

We have been coming to the South Cape Diner for several years. We went back the first day opened when they were at 25% capacity and we were very pleased with the procedures for safety they were using. Went back the second week and to be very honest it will be the last time to spend our money there. They changed their protocols. Left condiments on table and offering coffee while cleaning others people's dirty dishes.  Brought ketchup and hot sauce in original bottles, not individual containers for safety. In addition, I believe it was either the owner or manager...he broke a neon sign and then loudly swore. There were several tables occupied. While frustrating I am sure, he should recognize he finally had paying customers in his establishment. To top it off, there was fruit flies everywhere...there was the previous week to but thought it might be a one off.  Given the COVID non safety procedures, literally swatting fruit flies when we ate, and the non professional manner of the manager, we will not be back. South Cape Diner, Cape Coral Pkwy, Cape Coral,Fl. Here is some chatter and my 2 cents on the food.  I have been here before and been a happy trooper. I decided on the comfort food.Meatloaf,mash taters and cole slaw. 10 bucks.....  Oh so wrong. First the cole slaw. Though it was fresh and crunchy it was just horrible with a very sour vinegar dressing.  There was no mash potatoe. The potatoe were out of the box with too much liquid... It was like eating runny malt-o-meal.  The gravy was box too.Tasted very good. Dark color but no bits of beef to be seen.  The meat loaf was like a slice of dark rye bread. Heavy tasted horrible.  I will be back but once a new cook is here.
